        <h2>Cat Care</h2>
        <p>Here are some general instructions on how to care for a cat:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Feeding:</strong> Feed your cat a balanced diet appropriate for their age, size, and health condition.</li>
            <li><strong>Hygiene:</strong> Keep your cat's litter box clean and provide fresh water daily.</li>
            <li><strong>Grooming:</strong> Brush your cat's coat regularly and trim their nails as needed.</li>
            <li><strong>Enrichment:</strong> Provide mental and physical stimulation through interactive toys and playtime.</li>
            <li><strong>Veterinary Care:</strong> Schedule regular check-ups with your veterinarian and keep up with vaccinations and preventive care.</li>
            <li><strong>Indoor Environment:</strong> Ensure your cat has a safe and comfortable indoor environment with places to hide, climb, and explore.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For more detailed information, you can visit <a href="https://www.aspca.org/pet-care/cat-care">ASPCA - Cat Care</a>.</p>
